<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-08-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-08-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="380" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d380">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.77/445</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Consul at Vladivostok</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJK1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-08-15"><hi rend="italic">August 15,
                                        1918</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>The American railway contingent which arrived Vladivostok August 11
                                was ordered there with the view of assisting in the reorganization
                                and operation of the Siberian Railway. It is hoped that it will
                                receive the support and cooperation of all political parties and
                                governmental factions. After communicating to officials this
                                telegram should be made public.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_LR1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>